  <mainContent><![CDATA[<h1>Governance</h1>
<p>The role of the Board is to agree policies and strategies for the college and to ensure it is able to monitor progress in their implementation. It also ensures the solvency of the college and the safeguarding of its assets. The Full Board of Governors normally meets four times each year in addition to holding two conferences. Much of the work of the Governors complete is carried out through its sub-committees: Finance &amp; General Purposes; Audit; Search &amp; Governance and Standards.</p>
<ul>
<li><a rel="noopener" data-udi="umb://media/c2b30f234e434b6381b6040f38685c3d" href="/media/1257/register-of-declared-interests-of-members-of-the-board-for-publication-on-website-2014.pdf" target="_blank" title="Register of Declared Interests 2014">Register of Declared Interests 2014/15</a></li>
<li><a data-udi="umb://media/bfefa63dbd1f48de9e03b44e324c0566" href="/media/1258/register-of-declared-interests-of-members-of-the-board-for-publication-on-website-2015-new-feb-update.pdf" title="Register of Declared Interests 2015">Register of Declared Interests 2015/16</a></li>
<li><a rel="noopener" data-udi="umb://media/8640f79b21cb4984a061c4499c968b8c" href="/media/1259/register-of-declared-interests-of-members-of-the-board-for-publication-on-website-2016.pdf" target="_blank" title="Register of Declared Interests 2016">Register of Declared Interests 2016/17</a></li>
</ul>
<h2>The USP College Governance</h2>
<p>The Seevic-Palmer’s Corporation</p>
<p>The Corporation’s function is to decide on strategic policy and the overall direction of the College.  Members of the Board work in collaboration with the leadership team to ensure the quality and effectiveness of provision that is offered to learners within the area.</p>
<p>The Seevic-Palmer’s Corporation will normally meet nine times a year.</p>
<p>The Corporation comprises of 15 members, including the Principal, two staff and two student members.</p>
<p><strong>List of members:</strong></p>
<p>Gordon Haines – Chair of the Corporation</p>
<p>Phillip Lennon – Vice Chair of the Corporation</p>
<p>Graeme Loveland – Vice Chair of the Corporation</p>
<p>Paul Bennett</p>
<p>Alex Dobinson</p>
<p>Shri Footring</p>
<p>Roger Key</p>
<p>Carol Skewes</p>
<p>Vacancy</p>
<p>Vacancy</p>
<p>Dan Pearson – Principal and Chief Executive</p>
<p>Ritchie Naylor – Staff Member</p>
<p>Vacancy – Staff Member</p>
<p>Daryl Cortez – Student Member</p>
<p>Aleisha Deller – Student Member</p>
<p><span>Clerk to the Corporation</span></p>
<p>If you would like further information about the Corporation, its work and current vacancies, please contact Sue Glover, Clerk to the Corporation at the college at<span> </span><a href="mailto:sue.glover@uspcollege.ac.uk">sue.glover@uspcollege.ac.uk</a></p>
<p><strong>Information</strong></p>
<p>Information about the college is generally available to the public on request. Any person wishing to view the following documents may do so by contacting the Clerk to the Governors. Single copies of many of these documents are normally available free of charge:</p>
<ul>
<li>Governing Body Standing Orders</li>
<li>Annual Report &amp; Financial Statements</li>
<li>The College Mission Statement &amp; Charter</li>
<li>College Prospectuses [directly from the College]</li>
<li>College Inspection Report [directly from the College]</li>
<li>Information on Student Achievements [directly from the College]</li>
<li>Registers of Interest of Governing Body Members and of Senior Staff with Significant Financial Responsibilities</li>
<li>Code of Conduct for Governing Body Members</li>
<li>Instruments &amp; Articles of Government</li>
</ul>
